style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To place a new ship or base in the galaxy, first
select the empire of the ship or base from the first drop-down list. Then s=
elect
the design of the ship or base from the second dropdown list.<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Once you have selecte=
d the
desired ship or base then left-click in the main view to place it.<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Some types of bases m=
ust be
placed at planets (e.g. mining stations and space ports). Other types of ba=
ses
can be placed anywhere in a system, or even in deep space (e.g. monitoring
stations).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If a ship is placed i=
n close
proximity to a planet then it will be parked in orbit at the planet until it
begins its first mission.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To create an abandone=
d ship,
unowned by any empire, first place a ship belonging to an empire. Then
double-click on the ship to edit it and change its empire to None.<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>

